    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{-y^{2}+4y+5}{y^{2}-25}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{y+1}{y+5}, y\ne 5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors.</p>
<p>If a polynomial is not in order, we order it by the variable<rsq/>s degrees.</p>
<p>If the leading coefficient is negative, we factor out <m>-1</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{-y^{2}+4y+5}{y^{2}-25}} \amp = \frac{{-\left(y^{2}-4y-5\right)}}{{y^{2}-25}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-5\right)}}{{\left(y-5\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{y+1}{y+5}, y\ne 5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y - 5</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne 5</m>.</p>
</solution>
